TITLE: Converting Feathers Query to Aggregation Pipeline in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how a standard Feathers query is converted to MongoDB aggregation pipeline stages. This includes matching, sorting, skipping, and limiting results.
SOURCE: https://github.com/feathersjs/feathers/blob/dove/docs/api/databases/mongodb.md#2025-04-17_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
const query = {
  text: { $regex: 'feathersjs', $options: 'igm' },
  $sort: { createdAt: -1 },
  $skip: 20,
  $limit: 10
}
```

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
;[
  // returns the set of records containing the word "feathersjs"
  { $match: { text: { $regex: 'feathersjs', $options: 'igm' } } },
  // Sorts the results of the previous step by newest messages, first.
  { $sort: { createdAt: -1 } },
  // Skips the first 20 records of the previous step
  { $skip: 20 },
  // returns the next 10 records
  { $limit: 10 }
]
```

