TITLE: Configuring Clustered Feathers.js Server with WebSocket Transport
DESCRIPTION: Server-side code to set up a Feathers.js application with clustering support using the socketio provider. This configuration restricts transport to websockets only to ensure successful handshakes across multiple worker processes.
SOURCE: https://github.com/feathersjs/feathers/blob/dove/docs/cookbook/general/scaling.md#2025-04-17_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import cluster from 'cluster';
import feathers from '@feathersjs/feathers';
import socketio from '@feathersjs/socketio';

const CLUSTER_COUNT = 4;

if (cluster.isMaster) {
  for (let i = 0; i < CLUSTER_COUNT; i++) {
    cluster.fork();
  }
} else {
  const app = feathers();
  // ensure the same worker handles websocket connections
  app.configure(socketio({
